job.content:
Our client is a public corporation focusing on technology development in Hong
Kong, they are seeking for a Senior Programmer/ Data engineer with solid
experience in .NET and ETL to join their team.

 

Responsibilities

 * Design and develop web-based user portal to support system integration;
 * Perform data preparation, cleansing and visualization by Azure OpenAI and
   PowerBI;
 * Discover and evaluate new technologies to support business needs and strategy
 * Work closely with product managers, designers, and developers to build highly
   scalable and available products;
 * Follow the priority of project managers in the entire agile SDLC to ensure
   the project objectives are achieved timely;
 * Perform unit and system integration tests with happy and exceptional cases;
 * Perform other jobs as assigned;


Experience

 * Min. 3 years of experience preferably in application development;
 * Solid experiences in .Net, node.js, Javascript, python and SQL programming;
 * Knowledge of ETL, data pipeline and data model implementation is a must;
 * Hands-on cloud and data platform (Preferably in Azure, Databricks and
   PowerBI) is a plus;
 * Experience in AI, prompt engineering and Web3 is a plus;
 * Detailed-minded and committed to success;
 * Strong sense of responsibility and eager to learn;
 * Good command of written and spoken Chinese and English;
 * Candidates with less experience will be considered as Programmer;

 

Education

 * Bachelor’s degree preferably in Computer Science / Information Technology /
   Software Engineering / Data Science or related disciplines;

 

Interested parties, please click to
https://www.adecco.com.hk/information-technology-i-t--jobs/data-engineer-senior-program/3631335

Please note that only short listed candidates will be notified. All information
gathered will be treated in strict confidence and solely used for recruitment
purposes

Responsibilities:

 * Performing survey duties as required;
 * Reviewing and providing technical input by using AutoCAD, MicroStation,
   OpenRoads Designer;
 * Verifying the accuracy of survey data, including measurements and
   calculations conducted at survey sites;
 * Preparing and document the survey results including data, charts, plots,
   maps, records, etc.

 

Requirements:

 * BSc/ HD in Geomatics / Land Surveying & Geo-Informatics;
 * Minimum 10 years job experience in land and civil works;
 * Corporate member of professional institution such as HKIS or equivalent
   (local or overseas);
 * Familiar in Land and Civil Engineering Surveying;
 * Proficiency in software application such as AutoCAD, MicroStation, OpenRoads
   Designer;
 * Good command in written and spoken Cantonese, Mandarin & English;
 * Candidates with less qualifications and experience will be considered as
   Deputy Chief Surveyor.

 

 

We provide attractive remuneration package, fringe benefits and excellent career
prospects to the right candidate. Interested parties please send your
application with full resume with availability and expected salary to Human
Resources Department by email bkhr.g@buildking.hk or by clicking "QUICK APPLY".

Build King is an equal opportunity employer. We respect the fundamental rights
of our employees and are committed to building an equal, diverse and inclusive
working environment, and providing equal opportunities in all aspects of
employment regardless of gender, race, ethnic origin, marital status, education
or disabilities. Please visit our website www.buildking.hk for more details.

